annotationA: Adenylate kinase; Catalyzes the reversible transfer of the terminal phosphate group between ATP and AMP. Plays an important role in cellular energy homeostasis and in adenine nucleotide metabolism. Adenylate kinase activity is critical for regulation of the phosphate utilization and the AMP de novo biosynthesis pathways; Belongs to the adenylate kinase family. AK2 subfamily
annotationB: Protein binding; AMP deaminase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: IMP salvage; Belongs to the metallo-dependent hydrolases superfamily. Adenosine and AMP deaminases family
